of their wealth and iewels, of their odours and perfumes, of their wines &amp; syrups, there is no offending chaste eares with their incredible customes: so vilde and filthy is their idolatry, so obscene and shamelesse their liues, so ridiculous their incantations, so exorbitant their presenting of virgins to be deflowred of Idols, so abominable their exorcismes, and so odious their sencelesse profanation, with lamentable obstinacy not to be diuerted: I will therefore leaue them to the supreame Iudge, and returne to England with this caution, that the foole hath sayd in his heart there is no God, and I hope wee attend these discoueries with feare or contempt.
                     
                     
