their kingdomes, courts, common-wealth, riches, pleasures, ciuill administration, and mightinesse: yet (as I take it) so farre from a conquest, as wee were ouer France, when we had only Callis in Picardy, or Turwin and Tornay, which cost more the re-edifying, then all the country about it was worth. Heere you shall also finde how they haue striued with the Aegyptians for antiquity and cunning, how many Ilands are subiected vnto them, amongst whom Summatra, in times past called Taprobana, mustreth the power of eight Kings. Iapan affoordeth our English a harbour; and at Bantam they receiue the commodities of China from the Indian Marchants, who are only admitted to commerce amongst them: and diuers others, as are therein variated with many particulars.
