or if you will, but Earles; who by their valours and heroik endeauours, obtained the noble Diadems of the world: the one was Godfrey, inuested King of Ierusalem, and made like another Agamemnon, Captaine Generall of the Christian army against the Saracens. The other was Stephen, sonne of Duke Williams daughter of Normandy, raised to the dignity of England, and maintaining the possession against Maud the Empresse and her sonne, during his life.
